@startuml
title SomeTrails Login / Register
actor User
participant "SomeTrails"         as ST
participant "Auth Page"          as AP
participant "Login Form"         as LF
participant "Register Form"      as RF
participant "Auth Server"        as AS
participant "User Database"      as DB
participant "Email Service"      as ES
participant "Subscription Svc"   as SUB
participant "Session Manager"    as SM

== Navigate to Auth ==
User -> ST   : Navigate to SomeTrails
ST   -> SM   : Check for active session
SM   --> ST  : No active session
ST   -> AP   : Show auth page

== Existing User - Log In ==
User -> AP   : Select "Log In"
AP   -> LF   : Display login form
User -> LF   : Enter email and password
LF   -> AS   : Submit credentials
AS   -> DB   : Verify credentials
DB   --> AS  : Credentials valid
AS   -> SM   : Create session
SM   --> AS  : Session token
AS   --> LF  : Login success
LF   --> ST  : Redirect to logged-in site

== Failed Login ==
User -> LF   : Enter invalid credentials
LF   -> AS   : Submit credentials
AS   -> DB   : Verify credentials
DB   --> AS  : Invalid
AS   --> LF  : Return error
LF   --> User: Show error message

== New User - Register ==
User -> AP   : Select "Register"
AP   -> RF   : Display registration form
User -> RF   : Enter email, password, username
RF   -> AS   : Submit registration
AS   -> DB   : Check email uniqueness
DB   --> AS  : Email available
AS   -> DB   : Create user record
DB   --> AS  : User created
AS   -> ES   : Send verification email
ES   --> User: Deliver verification link
AS   -> SM   : Create session
SM   --> AS  : Session token
AS   --> RF  : Registration success

== Offer Subscription ==
RF   -> SUB  : Initiate subscription offer
SUB  --> User: Present tier options (Base/Plus/Peak)
User -> SUB  : Select tier
SUB  --> ST  : Redirect to logged-in site

== Password Reset ==
User -> LF   : Click "Forgot password"
LF   -> AS   : Request reset
AS   -> DB   : Lookup email
DB   --> AS  : User found
AS   -> ES   : Send reset email
ES   --> User: Deliver reset link
User -> AS   : Submit new password via link
AS   -> DB   : Update password hash
DB   --> AS  : Updated
AS   --> User: Confirm reset

@enduml
